---
import EventNav from "../../components/activate-ri/EventNav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Notice from "../../components/Notice.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Activate All RI 2026 Help"
  description="Help for Activate All RI 2026 activator plans, coverage, time blocks, and private edit links."
  canonicalPath="/activate-ri-2026/help/"
>
  <SiteHeader variant="solid" showEventLink />
  <main id="main">
    <section class="section event-page" aria-labelledby="help-title">
      <div class="container">
        <EventNav />
        <div class="section-header">
          <p class="eyebrow">Activator help</p>
          <h1 id="help-title">Activate RI help</h1>
          <p class="lead">
            Use this page when you are not sure what the signup form is asking
            for, what happens after you submit, or how private edit links work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="event-guidance event-guidance--stacked">
          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-event-title">
            <h2 id="help-event-title">What is Activate All RI 2026?</h2>
            <p>
              Activate All RI 2026 is an unofficial Rhode Island POTA community
              effort to coordinate planned activations for all 61 Rhode Island
              references during one event window. The schedule helps activators
              see coverage gaps and helps hunters find planned activity.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-coverage-title">
            <h2 id="help-coverage-title">What does coverage mean?</h2>
            <p>
              Coverage means someone has shared a planned activation window for
              that reference. It is not an official park reservation, does not
              prevent another activator from operating there, and does not
              guarantee that contacts will be made.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-time-title">
            <h2 id="help-time-title">How should I choose a time block?</h2>
            <p>
              Pick the three-hour block closest to when you expect to be on the
              air. The block is a planning tool for the public schedule, not a
              promise to operate for exactly three hours. If your timing
              changes, use your private edit link to update the plan.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-notes-title">
            <h2 id="help-notes-title">What should go in public notes?</h2>
            <p>
              Public notes are shown to hunters. Useful notes include parking or
              access details, QRP or portable context, and the order of stops in
              a rove. Do not put private contact details
              in public notes.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-link-title">
            <h2 id="help-link-title">What is the private edit link?</h2>
            <p>
              After you submit a plan, the site emails a private link to the
              address on your submission. That link lets you manage plans tied
              to the same email address, including changing stops, dates, time
              blocks, bands, modes, notes, or cancelling a plan. The volunteer
              page has more detail on
              <a href="/activate-ri-2026/volunteer/#use-your-edit-link-when-plans-change">
                using your edit link when plans change</a>.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-approval-title">
            <h2 id="help-approval-title">What happens after organizer review?</h2>
            <p>
              New plans wait for organizer review before they appear on the
              public schedule. After a plan is approved, activator edits are
              meant to keep the public schedule current without requiring a new
              signup.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-resend-title">
            <h2 id="help-resend-title">How do I get a new edit link?</h2>
            <p>
              Use the resend form on the
              <a href="/activate-ri-2026/volunteer/#use-your-edit-link-when-plans-change">
                volunteer page</a>
              with the callsign and email address from your signup. If you
              mistyped your email address, contact an organizer so they can help
              connect the plan to a reachable address.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="event-guidance__item" aria-labelledby="help-official-title">
            <h2 id="help-official-title">What remains official POTA?</h2>
            <p>
              ripota.org is a community coordination site. Official Parks on the
              Air resources remain authoritative for rules, references, accounts,
              spots, logs, awards, and whether an activation is valid.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <Notice />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
